{"title_page": "Food truck rally", "text_new": "[[File:LentSpace - Food trucks.jpg|right|thumb|Food trucks gather at [[LentSpace]] in New York City in 2012]]\n\nA '''food truck rally''' (also called a '''food truck festival''', '''food truck rodeo''',<ref name=\"rodeo1\">(9 June 2013). [http://www.newsobserver.com/2013/06/09/2951063/raleigh-food-truck-rodeo-corrals.html Raleigh food truck rodeo corrals hungry crowd], ''Raleigh News and Observer''</ref><ref name=\"durhamnc\">(3 September 2012). [http://www.newsobserver.com/2012/09/03/2312727/awesomeness-makes-food-truck-rodeo.html 'Awesomeness' makes food-truck rodeo a hit], ''Raleigh News and Observer''</ref> '''food truck gathering''', or similar names) is an event where a group of [[food truck]]s gather in one location.\n\nThe events typically feature \"modern\" food trucks emphasizing food quality and variety, a trend which has grown significantly in popularity in the [[United States]] since approximately 2008.  Formal gatherings of food trucks as an event in the United States began in 2010.  The first LA Food Fest, held in February 2010, appears to have been one of the earliest such events.<ref name=\"mash1\">Buck, Stephanie (4 August 2011). [http://mashable.com/2011/08/04/food-truck-history-infographic/ The Rise of the Social Food Truck], ''[[Mashable]]''</ref><ref name=\"latimes1\">(14 February 2010). [http://articles.latimes.com/2010/feb/14/local/la-me-streetfood14-2010feb14 LA Street Food Fest attracts thousands], ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' (reporting on \"first annual\" LA Street Food Fest held in February 2010, with about 30 trucks)</ref><ref name=\"boston1\">(9 August 2010). [http://radioboston.wbur.org/2010/08/09/more-food-trucks Mayor Menino Understands: Bostonians Want More Food Trucks], ''[[WBUR]]'' (report in wake of \"First Annual Boston Food Truck Festival\" held in August 2010)</ref><ref name=\"offthegrid1\">(1 October 2011). [https://www.nytimes.com/2011/10/02/us/the-food-truck-revolution-revs-up-with-a-little-help.html?pagewanted=all&_r=0 The Food Truck Revolution Revs Up, With a Little Help], ''[[The New York Times]]'' (reporting on the \"Off the Grid\" gathering in San Francisco which began in June 2010)</ref><ref name=\"miami1st\">(15 August 2011). [http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/2011-08-15/news/fl-hollywood-food-truck-invasion-20110815_1_trucks-gourmet-grilled-cheese-artspark Weekly Food Truck Invasion hits Hollywood], ''[[Sun Sentinel]]'' (first Miami gathering of 12 trucks occurred in September 2010)</ref>\n\n[[Tampa]], [[Florida]], which has been a [[Food trucks in Tampa, Florida|popular area for food trucks]] and hosted its first food truck event in September 2011,<ref name=\"creati1\">(24 August 2011). [http://cltampa.com/dailyloaf/archives/2011/08/24/tampas-first-food-truck-rally-is-a-go-sat-sept-24th Tampa's first 'Food Truck Rally' is a go! - Sat., Sept. 24th], ''Creative Loafing''</ref>  hosted a rally with 121 food trucks in March 2014, said to be a new world record, breaking the prior record of 99 set in Tampa in September 2013.<ref name=\"tamp2\">(30 March 2014). [http://www.wtsp.com/story/news/local/2014/03/30/tampa-worlds-largest-food-truck-rally-guinness-record/7079805/ Tampa food truck rally sets new Guinness record], ''WTSP'' ([[Associated Press]] story)</ref><ref name=\"99one\">(3 September 2013). [http://tbo.com/dining/record-tampa-food-truck-rally-creates-taste-for-bigger-one-20130903/ Record Tampa food truck rally creates taste for bigger one], ''[[Tampa Tribune]]''</ref>  Prior to that, an April 2013 \"food truck parade\" in Miami<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://modentechgadgets.blogspot.com/2020/04/top-gadgets-in-kitchen.html|title=Top 7 gadgets in Kitchen|website=Top 7 gadgets in Kitchen|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>, with 62 trucks, was declared the largest to date.<ref name=\"miami3\">(24 April 2013). [http://blogs.miaminewtimes.com/shortorder/2013/04/magic_city_casino_sets_guinnes.php Magic City Casino Sets Guinness World Record for Food Truck Parade], ''Miami New Times''</ref> In 2018, [[Chicago Food Truck Festival]] planned to have over 50 food trucks in Chicago.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/ct-ent-food-truck-fest-0621-story.html |title=Get ready, Chicago foodies: Chicago Food Truck Festival will host new, unique flavors on wheels |newspaper=Chicago Tribune |accessdate=2018-07-11}}</ref> Also, in 2018 more than 50 food trucks rallied in Meridian Township.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lansingstatejournal.com/story/news/2018/06/27/more-than-50-food-trucks-roll-into-meridian-township-june-29/734072002/ |title=More than 50 food trucks roll into Meridian Township on June 30 |publisher=Lansingstatejournal.com |date= |accessdate=2018-07-11}}</ref> Also, in 2018, in Muskeon Michigan a food truck rally of 23 food trucks occurred.<ref>{{cite web|author=On Air 4:25AM |url=https://www.wzzm13.com/article/news/local/muskegon/first-of-three-summer-food-truck-rallies-in-muskegon/69-568256771 |title=First of three summer food truck rallies in Muskegon |publisher=wzzm13.com |date=2018-06-27 |accessdate=2018-07-11}}</ref> In June 2018, over 30 food trucks rallied in Daytona.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.daytondailynews.com/events/new-event-more-than-food-trucks-join-darke-county-first-food-truck-rally-and-competition/TgSOG79mm1dmYikOwEk8TL/|title=New Event: More than 30 food trucks join Darke County\u2019s first food truck rally and competition|newspaper=Dayton Daily News|accessdate=11 July 2018}}</ref> Furthermore, there are more food truck rallies occurring throughout the US.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bestproducts.com/fun-things-to-do/a1105/food-truck-festival-guide/ |title=9 Best Food Truck Festivals & Events in the US - Food Truck Festival Guide 2018 |publisher=Bestproducts.com |date=2018-04-23 |accessdate=2018-07-11}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n{{portalbar|Food|Transport}}\n{{Street food}}\n\n[[Category:Fast food]]\n[[Category:Food and drink festivals in the United States]]\n[[Category:Food trucks]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:LentSpace - Food trucks.jpg|right|thumb|Food trucks gather at [[LentSpace]] in New York City in 2012]]\n\nA '''food truck rally''' (also called a '''food truck festival''', '''food truck rodeo''',<ref name=\"rodeo1\">(9 June 2013). [http://www.newsobserver.com/2013/06/09/2951063/raleigh-food-truck-rodeo-corrals.html Raleigh food truck rodeo corrals hungry crowd], ''Raleigh News and Observer''</ref><ref name=\"durhamnc\">(3 September 2012). [http://www.newsobserver.com/2012/09/03/2312727/awesomeness-makes-food-truck-rodeo.html 'Awesomeness' makes food-truck rodeo a hit], ''Raleigh News and Observer''</ref> '''food truck gathering''', or similar names) is an event where a group of [[food truck]]s gather in one location.\n\nThe events typically feature \"modern\" food trucks emphasizing food quality and variety, a trend which has grown significantly in popularity in the [[United States]] since approximately 2008.  Formal gatherings of food trucks as an event in the United States began in 2010.  The first LA Food Fest, held in February 2010, appears to have been one of the earliest such events.<ref name=\"mash1\">Buck, Stephanie (4 August 2011). [http://mashable.com/2011/08/04/food-truck-history-infographic/ The Rise of the Social Food Truck], ''[[Mashable]]''</ref><ref name=\"latimes1\">(14 February 2010). [http://articles.latimes.com/2010/feb/14/local/la-me-streetfood14-2010feb14 LA Street Food Fest attracts thousands], ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' (reporting on \"first annual\" LA Street Food Fest held in February 2010, with about 30 trucks)</ref><ref name=\"boston1\">(9 August 2010). [http://radioboston.wbur.org/2010/08/09/more-food-trucks Mayor Menino Understands: Bostonians Want More Food Trucks], ''[[WBUR]]'' (report in wake of \"First Annual Boston Food Truck Festival\" held in August 2010)</ref><ref name=\"offthegrid1\">(1 October 2011). [https://www.nytimes.com/2011/10/02/us/the-