{"title_page": "Marcin Mo\u017cd\u017conek", "text_new": "{{Infobox volleyball biography\n| name           = Marcin Mo\u017cd\u017conek\n| image          = Marcin Mo\u017cd\u017conek 2010-10-30.jpg\n| image_size     = <!-- Leave this blank for the default size -->\n| caption        = \n| fullname       = Marcin Rafa\u0142 Mo\u017cd\u017conek\n| nickname       = ''Mo\u017cd\u017con''\n| nationality    = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Poland|Polish]]\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1985|2|9|mf=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Olsztyn]], [[Poland]]\n| death_date     = <!-- Use  {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}}   -->\n| death_place    = \n| hometown       = \n| height         = {{height|m=2.11|precision=0}}\n| weight         = \n| spike          = \n| block          = \n| college        = \n| position       = Middle blocker\n| currentclub    = \n| currentnumber  = \n| years          = 2001\u20132004<br>2004\u20132008<br>2008\u20132012<br>2012\u20132014<br>2014\u20132015<br>2015\u20132016<br>2016\u20132020\n| teams          = {{flagicon|POL}} SMS PZPS Spa\u0142a<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[AZS Olsztyn]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]]<br> {{flagicon|TUR}} [[Halkbank Ankara]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[MKS Cuprum Lubin]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]\n| nationalyears  = 2007\u20132016\n| nationalteam   = {{vb|POL}} <small>(242)</small>\n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalCountry|{{POL}}}}\n{{MedalSport|Men's [[volleyball]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|World Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2014 FIVB Men's World Championship|2014 Poland]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|World Cup]]}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2011 FIVB Men's World Cup|2011 Japan]]|}}\n{{Medal|Bronze|[[2015 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|2015 Japan]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Men's European Volleyball Championship|European Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold| [[2009 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2009 Turkey]] |}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2011 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2011 Austria/Czech Republic]] |}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIVB World League|World League]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|2012 Sofia]]|}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[FIVB World League 2011|2011 Gda\u0144sk]]|}}\n}}\n'''Marcin Mo\u017cd\u017conek''' (born 9 February 1985) is a former [[Poland|Polish]] [[volleyball player]], a member of the [[Poland men's national volleyball team]] in 2007\u20132016, a participant of the [[Olympic Games]] ([[2008 Summer Olympics|Beijing 2008]], [[2012 Summer Olympics|London 2012]]), [[2014 FIVB Men's World Championship|2014 World Champion]], [[2009 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2009 European Champion]], a gold medalist of the [[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|2012 World League]], silver medalist of the [[2011 FIVB Men's World Cup|2011 World Cup]], bronze medalist of the [[FIVB World League 2011|2011 World League]] and [[2011 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2011 European Championship]], three\u2013time [[PlusLiga|Polish Champion]] ([[2008\u201309 PlusLiga|2009]], [[2009\u201310 PlusLiga|2010]], [[2010\u201311 PlusLiga|2011]]).\n\n[[File:Marcin Mo\u017cd\u017conek (1).jpg|thumb|Marcin Mo\u017cd\u017conek after match [[Poland men's national volleyball team|Poland]]-[[United States men's national volleyball team|USA]] at [[Spodek]] in [[Katowice]] ([[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|World League 2012]]).]]\n[[File:Marcin Mo\u017cd\u017conek (8087188024).jpg|thumb|Mo\u017cd\u017conek as player of [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]] in 2012.]]\n\n==Career==\n\n===Clubs===\nIn 2012-2014 Mo\u017cd\u017conek played for [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]].<ref>[http://eurosport.onet.pl/siatkowka/reprezentacje/marcin-mozdzonek-nowym-zawodnikiem-zaksa-kedzierzyn-kozle/8whvs ''Marcin Mo\u017cd\u017conek nowym zawodnikiem ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale''] \u2013 eurosport.onet.pl \u2013 03-07-2012</ref> With this club he won the Polish Cup twice (2013, 2014) and won the silver medal in the Polish Championship 2012/2013. In October 2014, he moved to Turkish club [[Halkbank Ankara]].<ref>[http://www.plusliga.pl/news/id/10034 ''Marcin Mo\u017cd\u017conek odchodzi z ZAKSY''] \u2013 plusliga.pl \u2013 11-10-2014</ref> On March 29, 2015 he achieved his first trophy with his new club [[Halkbank Ankara]] \u2013 the Turkish Cup. In the final his team beat [[Arkas Spor|Arkas Izmir]] 3-0 and he scored 10 points.<ref>[http://www.worldofvolley.com/News/Latest_news/Turkey/49873/turkish-cup-m-halkbank-clinched-the-trophy.html ''TURKISH CUP M: HalkBank clinched the trophy!''] \u2013 worldofvolley.com \u2013 29-03-2015</ref> In July 2015 he came back to Poland and he signed a contract with [[MKS Cuprum Lubin]].\n\n===National team===\nHe debuted in the Polish national team in 2007 (during the [[Poland men's national volleyball team|Poland]] - [[Argentina men's national volleyball team|Argentina]] match). Mo\u017cd\u017conek was in the Polish squad when the Polish national team won the gold medal at the [[2009 Men's European Volleyball Championship|European Championship 2009]].<ref>[http://www.cev.eu/Competition-Area/CompetitionMatches.aspx?ID=387 ''2009 CEV European Championships Results''] \u2013 cev.eu \u2013 03-09-2009</ref> On September 14, 2009 he was awarded The [[Order of Polonia Restituta]].<ref>[http://www.prezydent.pl/aktywnosc/ordery-i-odznaczenia/art,695,reprezentacja-siatkarzy-odznaczona-przez-prezydenta.html ''Reprezentacja siatkarzy odznaczona przez prezydenta''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140309231119/http://www.prezydent.pl/aktywnosc/ordery-i-odznaczenia/art%2C695%2Creprezentacja-siatkarzy-odznaczona-przez-prezydenta.html |date=2014-03-09 }} \u2013 prezydent.pl \u2013 15-09-2009</ref> The Order was conferred on the following day by the Prime Minister of Poland, [[Donald Tusk]]. With the Polish team, he won three medals in 2011 - silver at [[2011 FIVB Men's World Cup|World Cup]]<ref>[http://www.fivb.org/EN/Volleyball/Competitions/WorldCup/2011/Men/viewPressRelease.asp?No=33340&Language=en ''Poland shoot up World Rankings on back of World Cup silver''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 06-12-2011</ref> and two bronzes at [[2011 FIVB Volleyball World League|World League]]<ref>[http://www.fivb.org/EN/Volleyball/Competitions/WorldLeague/2011/FIVB_WorldLeague_FinalReport_2011/#/78/ ''2011 FIVB Volleyball World League Final Report''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 10-07-2011</ref> and [[2011 Men's European Volleyball Championship|European Championship]].<ref>[http://www.cev.eu/Competition-Area/CompetitionNews.aspx?NewsID=10999&ID=14 ''Bartosz Kurek is the man of the day as Poland strikes bronze at EuroVolley''] \u2013 cev.eu \u2013 18-09-2011</ref> In November 2011 he was declared the new captain of national team.<ref>[http://www.plusliga.pl/news/id/4899/Kapitan_Mozdzonek//csort/creationDate/corder/desc/cpage/3 ''Kapitan Mo\u017cd\u017conek''] \u2013 plusliga.pl \u2013 11-11-2011</ref> He is a gold medalist of [[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|World League 2012]] in [[Sofia]], [[Bulgaria]].<ref>[http://www.fivb.org/EN/Volleyball/Competitions/WorldLeague/2012/viewPressRelease.asp?No=35977&Language=en# ''Poland beat USA to claim first World League title''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 08-07-2012</ref><ref>[http://www.fivb.org/EN/Volleyball/Competitions/WorldLeague/2012/viewPressRelease.asp?No=35974&Language=en# ''Poland wins historical gold at the 2012 World League''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 08-07-2012</ref> In May 2014 he was replaced as captain by [[Micha\u0142 Winiarski]]. On September 21, 2014 Poland won the title of [[2014 FIVB Men's World Championship|World Champion 2014]].<ref>[http://www.fivb.org/viewPressRelease.asp?No=49498&Language=en#.VCAG_qIu6ho ''Poland win second World Championship title at home''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 21-09-2014</ref><ref>[http://www.fivb.org/viewPressRelease.asp?No=49500&Language=en#.VCAHAaIu6ho ''Poland put an end to the reign of Brazil''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 21-09-2014</ref><ref>[http://www.plusliga.pl/news/id/9914 ''FIVB M\u015a Polska 2014: Polska ze z\u0142otym medalem''] \u2013 plusliga.pl \u2013 21-09-2014</ref> On October 27, 2014, he received a state award granted by the Polish President, [[Bronis\u0142aw Komorowski]]: the [[Order of Polonia Restituta|Officer's Cross of Polonia Restituta]] ''for outstanding sports achievements and the promotion of Poland in the world''.<ref>[http://www.prezydent.pl/aktualnosci/ordery-i-odznaczenia/art,1382,dziekuje-za-chwile-wzruszenia-i-dumy.html ''\"Dzi\u0119kuj\u0119 za chwile wzruszenia i dumy\"''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141027165935/http://www.prezydent.pl/aktualnosci/ordery-i-odznaczenia/art%2C1382%2Cdziekuje-za-chwile-wzruszenia-i-dumy.html |date=2014-10-27 }} \u2013 prezydent.pl - 27-10-2014</ref>\n\nHe was not called to the national team by [[Stephane Antiga]] for the [[2016 Summer Olympics|2016 Olympic Games]] in [[Rio de Janeiro]].<ref>[http://www.przegladsportowy.pl/siatkowka,rio-2016-mozdzonek-i-wojtaszek-nie-jada-na-igrzyska-olimpijskie-,artykul,701228,1,282.html ''Rio 2016: Mo\u017cd\u017conek i Wojtaszek nie jad\u0105 na igrzyska olimpijskie''] \u2013 przegladsportowy.pl \u2013 14-07-2016</ref>\n\n==Sporting achievements==\n* '''[[CEV Champions League]]'''\n** [[File:Bronze medal europe.svg|16px]] [[Men's CEV Champions League 2009\u201310|2009/2010]] \u2013 with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** [[File:Silver medal europe.svg|16px]] [[Men's CEV Champions League 2011\u201312|2011/2012]] \u2013 with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n\n* '''[[FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|FIVB Club World Championship]]'''\n** [[File:Silver medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2009 FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|Qatar 2009]] \u2013 with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** [[File:Silver medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2010 FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|Qatar 2010]] \u2013 with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n\n* '''National championships'''\n** '''2004/2005''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2004\u201305 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[AZS Olsztyn]]\n** '''2005/2006''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2005\u201306 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[AZS Olsztyn]]\n** '''2006/2007''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2006\u201307 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[AZS Olsztyn]]\n** '''2007/2008''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2007\u201308 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[AZS Olsztyn]]\n** '''2008/2009''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Polish Cup, with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2008/2009''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2008\u201309 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2009/2010''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2009\u201310 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2010/2011''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Polish Cup, with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2010/2011''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2010\u201311 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2011/2012''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Polish Cup, with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2011/2012''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2011\u201312 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2012/2013''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Polish Cup, with [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]]\n** '''2012/2013''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2012\u201313 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]]\n** '''2013/2014''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Polish Cup, with [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]]\n** '''2014/2015''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Turkish Cup, with [[Halkbank Ankara]]\n** '''2014/2015''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] Turkish Championship, with [[Halkbank Ankara]]\n\n* '''National team'''\n** '''2003''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2003 European Youth Summer Olympic Festival|European Youth Olympic Festival]]\n** '''2003''' [[File:Gold medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2003 FIVB Volleyball Men's U21 World Championship|FIVB U21 World Championship]]\n** '''2009''' [[File:Gold medal europe.svg|16px]] [[2009 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]]\n** '''2011''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2011 FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League]]\n** '''2011''' [[File:Bronze medal europe.svg|16px]] [[2011 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]]\n** '''2011''' [[File:Simple silver cup.svg|16px]] [[2011 FIVB Men's World Cup|FIVB World Cup]]\n** '''2012''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League]]\n** '''2014''' [[File:Gold medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2014 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|FIVB World Championship]]\n** '''2015''' [[File:Simple bronze cup.svg|16px]] [[2015 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|FIVB World Cup]]\n\n===Individually===\n* '''2009:''' [[2009 FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|FIVB Club World Championship]] \u2013 Best Blocker\n* '''2011:''' [[2011 FIVB Men's World Cup|FIVB World Cup]] \u2013 Best Blocker\n* '''2012:''' Polish Cup \u2013 Best Blocker\n* '''2012:''' [[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League]] \u2013 Best Blocker\n* '''2013:''' [[2013 Memorial of Hubert Jerzy Wagner|Memorial of Hubert Jerzy Wagner]] \u2013 Best Blocker\n\n===State awards===\n* '''2009''' [[File:POL Polonia Restituta Kawalerski BAR.svg|60px|Ribbon]] [[Order of Polonia Restituta|Knight's Cross of Polonia Restituta]]\n* '''2014''' [[File:POL Polonia Restituta Oficerski BAR.svg|60px|Ribbon]] [[Order of Polonia Restituta|Officer's Cross of Polonia Restituta]]<ref>[http://isap.sejm.gov.pl/DetailsServlet?id=WMP20150000014 ''Postanowienie Prezydenta Rzeczypospolitej Polskiej z dnia 23 pa\u017adziernika 2014 r. o nadaniu order\u00f3w i odznacze\u0144''] \u2013 isap.sejm.gov.pl \u2013 23-10-2014</ref>\n* '''2014''' [[Honorary citizenship]] of [[Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.fivb.org/EN/volleyball/competitions/WorldLeague/2013/Players.asp?Tourn=WL2013&Team=POL&No=113018 FIVB Profile]\n* [http://www.plusliga.pl/players/id/83 PlusLiga player profile]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{S-sports}}\n{{succession box\n| before = [[Piotr Gruszka]]\n| after  = [[Micha\u0142 Winiarski]]\n| title  = [[Poland men's national volleyball team|Poland]] captain\n| years  = November 2011 \u2013 May 2014\n}}\n{{s-ach|aw}}\n{{succession box |\n  | before = \u2013\n  | after = {{flagicon|IRI}} [[Mohammad Mousavi (volleyball)|Mohammad Mousavi]]\n  | title = Best Blocker of <br>[[2009 FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|FIVB Club World Championship]]\n  | years = [[2009 FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|2009]]\n|}}\n{{succession box |\n  | before = {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Jos\u00e9 Luis Molt\u00f3]]\n  | after = {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Sebastian Sole]]<br />{{flagicon|IRI}} [[Mohammad Mousavi (volleyball)|Mohammad Mousavi]]\n  | title = Best Blocker of <br>[[FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|FIVB World Cup]]\n  | years = [[2011 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|2011]]\n|}}\n{{succession box |\n  | before = {{flagicon|RUS}} [[Maxim Mikhaylov]]\n  | after = {{flagicon|RUS}} [[Dmitriy Muserskiy]]<br>{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Emanuele Birarelli]]\n  | title = Best Blocker of <br>[[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League]]\n  | years = [[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|2012]]\n|}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w team}}\n{{Navboxes colour\n|title       = Poland squads\n|bg          = #DC143C\n|fg          = #ffffff\n|bordercolor = #Red\n|list1       =\n{{Poland men volleyball team 2008 Olympics}}\n{{Poland men volleyball team 2009 European Championships}}\n{{Poland men volleyball team 2011 World Cup}}\n{{Poland men volleyball team 2012 World League}}\n{{Poland men volleyball team 2012 Olympics}}\n{{Poland men volleyball team 2014 FIVB World Championship}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mozdzonek, Marcin}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Olsztyn]]\n[[Category:Polish men's volleyball players]]\n[[Category:Olympic volleyball players of Poland]]\n[[Category:Volleyball players at the 2008 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Volleyball players at the 2012 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Polish Champions of men's volleyball]]\n[[Category:AZS Olsztyn players]]\n[[Category:Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w players]]\n[[Category:ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale players]]\n[[Category:Halkbank volleyball players]]\n[[Category:Knights of the Order of Polonia Restituta]]\n[[Category:Officers of the Order of Polonia Restituta]]\n[[Category:Cuprum Lubin players]]\n[[Category:Polish expatriates in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Expatriate volleyball players in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox volleyball biography\n| name           = Marcin Mo\u017cd\u017conek\n| image          = Marcin Mo\u017cd\u017conek 2010-10-30.jpg\n| image_size     = <!-- Leave this blank for the default size -->\n| caption        = \n| fullname       = Marcin Rafa\u0142 Mo\u017cd\u017conek\n| nickname       = ''Mo\u017cd\u017con''\n| nationality    = {{flagicon|POL}} [[Poland|Polish]]\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1985|2|9|mf=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Olsztyn]], [[Poland]]\n| death_date     = <!-- Use  {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}}   -->\n| death_place    = \n| hometown       = \n| height         = {{height|m=2.11|precision=0}}\n| weight         = \n| spike          = \n| block          = \n| college        = \n| position       = Middle blocker\n| currentclub    = \n| currentnumber  = \n| years          = 2001\u20132004<br>2004\u20132008<br>2008\u20132012<br>2012\u20132014<br>2014\u20132015<br>2015\u20132016<br>2016\u20132020\n| teams          = {{flagicon|POL}} SMS PZPS Spa\u0142a<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]]<br> {{flagicon|TUR}} [[Halkbank Ankara]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[MKS Cuprum Lubin]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[Asseco Resovia Rzesz\u00f3w]]\n| nationalyears  = 2007\u20132016\n| nationalteam   = {{vb|POL}} <small>(242)</small>\n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalCountry|{{POL}}}}\n{{MedalSport|Men's [[volleyball]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIVB Volleyball Men's World Championship|World Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2014 FIVB Men's World Championship|2014 Poland]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|World Cup]]}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2011 FIVB Men's World Cup|2011 Japan]]|}}\n{{Medal|Bronze|[[2015 FIVB Volleyball Men's World Cup|2015 Japan]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Men's European Volleyball Championship|European Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold| [[2009 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2009 Turkey]] |}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2011 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2011 Austria/Czech Republic]] |}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FIVB World League|World League]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|2012 Sofia]]|}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[FIVB World League 2011|2011 Gda\u0144sk]]|}}\n}}\n'''Marcin Mo\u017cd\u017conek''' (born 9 February 1985) is a former [[Poland|Polish]] [[volleyball player]], a member of the [[Poland men's national volleyball team]] in 2007\u20132016, a participant of the [[Olympic Games]] ([[2008 Summer Olympics|Beijing 2008]], [[2012 Summer Olympics|London 2012]]), [[2014 FIVB Men's World Championship|2014 World Champion]], [[2009 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2009 European Champion]], a gold medalist of the [[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|2012 World League]], silver medalist of the [[2011 FIVB Men's World Cup|2011 World Cup]], bronze medalist of the [[FIVB World League 2011|2011 World League]] and [[2011 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2011 European Championship]], three\u2013time [[PlusLiga|Polish Champion]] ([[2008\u201309 PlusLiga|2009]], [[2009\u201310 PlusLiga|2010]], [[2010\u201311 PlusLiga|2011]]).\n\n[[File:Marcin Mo\u017cd\u017conek (1).jpg|thumb|Marcin Mo\u017cd\u017conek after match [[Poland men's national volleyball team|Poland]]-[[United States men's national volleyball team|USA]] at [[Spodek]] in [[Katowice]] ([[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|World League 2012]]).]]\n[[File:Marcin Mo\u017cd\u017conek (8087188024).jpg|thumb|Mo\u017cd\u017conek as player of [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]] in 2012.]]\n\n==Career==\n\n===Clubs===\nIn 2012-2014 Mo\u017cd\u017conek played for [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale]].<ref>[http://eurosport.onet.pl/siatkowka/reprezentacje/marcin-mozdzonek-nowym-zawodnikiem-zaksa-kedzierzyn-kozle/8whvs ''Marcin Mo\u017cd\u017conek nowym zawodnikiem ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale''] \u2013 eurosport.onet.pl \u2013 03-07-2012</ref> With this club he won the Polish Cup twice (2013, 2014) and won the silver medal in the Polish Championship 2012/2013. In October 2014, he moved to Turkish club [[Halkbank Ankara]].<ref>[http://www.plusliga.pl/news/id/10034 ''Marcin Mo\u017cd\u017conek odchodzi z ZAKSY''] \u2013 plusliga.pl \u2013 11-10-2014</ref> On March 29, 2015 he achieved his first trophy with his new club [[Halkbank Ankara]] \u2013 the Turkish Cup. In the final his team beat [[Arkas Spor|Arkas Izmir]] 3-0 and he scored 10 points.<ref>[http://www.worldofvolley.com/News/Latest_news/Turkey/49873/turkish-cup-m-halkbank-clinched-the-trophy.html ''TURKISH CUP M: HalkBank clinched the trophy!''] \u2013 worldofvolley.com \u2013 29-03-2015</ref> In July 2015 he came back to Poland and he signed a contract with [[MKS Cuprum Lubin]].\n\n===National team===\nHe debuted in the Polish national team in 2007 (during the [[Poland men's national volleyball team|Poland]] - [[Argentina men's national volleyball team|Argentina]] match). Mo\u017cd\u017conek was in the Polish squad when the Polish national team won the gold medal at the [[2009 Men's European Volleyball Championship|European Championship 2009]].<ref>[http://www.cev.eu/Competition-Area/CompetitionMatches.aspx?ID=387 ''2009 CEV European Championships Results''] \u2013 cev.eu \u2013 03-09-2009</ref> On September 14, 2009 he was awarded The [[Order of Polonia Restituta]].<ref>[http://www.prezydent.pl/aktywnosc/ordery-i-odznaczenia/art,695,reprezentacja-siatkarzy-odznaczona-przez-prezydenta.html ''Reprezentacja siatkarzy odznaczona przez prezydenta''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140309231119/http://www.prezydent.pl/aktywnosc/ordery-i-odznaczenia/art%2C695%2Creprezentacja-siatkarzy-odznaczona-przez-prezydenta.html |date=2014-03-09 }} \u2013 prezydent.pl \u2013 15-09-2009</ref> The Order was conferred on the following day by the Prime Minister of Poland, [[Donald Tusk]]. With the Polish team, he won three medals in 2011 - silver at [[2011 FIVB Men's World Cup|World Cup]]<ref>[http://www.fivb.org/EN/Volleyball/Competitions/WorldCup/2011/Men/viewPressRelease.asp?No=33340&Language=en ''Poland shoot up World Rankings on back of World Cup silver''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 06-12-2011</ref> and two bronzes at [[2011 FIVB Volleyball World League|World League]]<ref>[http://www.fivb.org/EN/Volleyball/Competitions/WorldLeague/2011/FIVB_WorldLeague_FinalReport_2011/#/78/ ''2011 FIVB Volleyball World League Final Report''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 10-07-2011</ref> and [[2011 Men's European Volleyball Championship|European Championship]].<ref>[http://www.cev.eu/Competition-Area/CompetitionNews.aspx?NewsID=10999&ID=14 ''Bartosz Kurek is the man of the day as Poland strikes bronze at EuroVolley''] \u2013 cev.eu \u2013 18-09-2011</ref> In November 2011 he was declared the new captain of national team.<ref>[http://www.plusliga.pl/news/id/4899/Kapitan_Mozdzonek//csort/creationDate/corder/desc/cpage/3 ''Kapitan Mo\u017cd\u017conek''] \u2013 plusliga.pl \u2013 11-11-2011</ref> He is a gold medalist of [[2012 FIVB Volleyball World League|World League 2012]] in [[Sofia]], [[Bulgaria]].<ref>[http://www.fivb.org/EN/Volleyball/Competitions/WorldLeague/2012/viewPressRelease.asp?No=35977&Language=en# ''Poland beat USA to claim first World League title''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 08-07-2012</ref><ref>[http://www.fivb.org/EN/Volleyball/Competitions/WorldLeague/2012/viewPressRelease.asp?No=35974&Language=en# ''Poland wins historical gold at the 2012 World League''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 08-07-2012</ref> In May 2014 he was replaced as captain by [[Micha\u0142 Winiarski]]. On September 21, 2014 Poland won the title of [[2014 FIVB Men's World Championship|World Champion 2014]].<ref>[http://www.fivb.org/viewPressRelease.asp?No=49498&Language=en#.VCAG_qIu6ho ''Poland win second World Championship title at home''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 21-09-2014</ref><ref>[http://www.fivb.org/viewPressRelease.asp?No=49500&Language=en#.VCAHAaIu6ho ''Poland put an end to the reign of Brazil''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 21-09-2014</ref><ref>[http://www.plusliga.pl/news/id/9914 ''FIVB M\u015a Polska 2014: Polska ze z\u0142otym medalem''] \u2013 plusliga.pl \u2013 21-09-2014</ref> On October 27, 2014, he received a state award granted by the Polish President, [[Bronis\u0142aw Komorowski]]: the [[Order of Polonia Restituta|Officer's Cross of Polonia Restituta]] ''for outstanding sports achievements and the promotion of Poland in the world''.<ref>[http://www.prezydent.pl/aktualnosci/ordery-i-odznaczenia/art,1382,dziekuje-za-chwile-wzruszenia-i-dumy.html ''\"Dzi\u0119kuj\u0119 za chwile wzruszenia i dumy\"''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141027165935/http://www.prezydent.pl/aktualnosci/ordery-i-odznaczenia/art%2C1382%2Cdziekuje-za-chwile-wzruszenia-i-dumy.html |date=2014-10-27 }} \u2013 prezydent.pl - 27-10-2014</ref>\n\nHe was not called to the national team by [[Stephane Antiga]] for the [[2016 Summer Olympics|2016 Olympic Games]] in [[Rio de Janeiro]].<ref>[http://www.przegladsportowy.pl/siatkowka,rio-2016-mozdzonek-i-wojtaszek-nie-jada-na-igrzyska-olimpijskie-,artykul,701228,1,282.html ''Rio 2016: Mo\u017cd\u017conek i Wojtaszek nie jad\u0105 na igrzyska olimpijskie''] \u2013 przegladsportowy.pl \u2013 14-07-2016</ref>\n\n==Sporting achievements==\n* '''[[CEV Champions League]]'''\n** [[File:Bronze medal europe.svg|16px]] [[Men's CEV Champions League 2009\u201310|2009/2010]] \u2013 with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** [[File:Silver medal europe.svg|16px]] [[Men's CEV Champions League 2011\u201312|2011/2012]] \u2013 with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n\n* '''[[FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|FIVB Club World Championship]]'''\n** [[File:Silver medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2009 FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|Qatar 2009]] \u2013 with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** [[File:Silver medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2010 FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|Qatar 2010]] \u2013 with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n\n* '''National championships'''\n** '''2004/2005''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2004\u201305 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn|AZS Olsztyn]]\n** '''2005/2006''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2005\u201306 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn|AZS Olsztyn]]\n** '''2006/2007''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2006\u201307 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn|AZS Olsztyn]]\n** '''2007/2008''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2007\u201308 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[Indykpol AZS Olsztyn|AZS Olsztyn]]\n** '''2008/2009''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Polish Cup, with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2008/2009''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2008\u201309 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [